    "username": "emollick",
    "nickname": "Ethan Mollick",
    "text": "Fiction writing is such a weird problem space with AI because fiction depends on you, as a reader, assuming meaning behind the writing. And AI is terrific at writing things with high levels of implied meaning. The more meaning you seek, the more you find, though it is illusory.",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/emollick/status/2030540410104561965",
    "time": "2026-03-08 15:05",
    "id_str": "2030540410104561965",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "emollick",
    "nickname": "Ethan Mollick",
    "text": "Like the AI generates absolute bangers of metaphor that make no sense, but, because the writing is meaning-like, you figure out ways for it to make sense, and through that interpretation, find something deeply meaningful\n\nVery indicative of the general problem of AI personality https://t.co/iw9aGeOEkA",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/emollick/status/2030541451306684706",
    "time": "2026-03-08 15:09",
    "id_str": "2030541451306684706",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "emollick",
    "nickname": "Ethan Mollick",
    "text": "Anyhow, the problem of the relationship between the reader and the text is now one of considerable practical import for understanding AI.\n\nThe return of the humanities!",
